#Tutorial.create("categories"=>"ebooks, social media, android sdk", "conclusion"=>"<h2>Start Learning With a Yearly Subscription</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://tutsplus.com/pricing?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Subscribe to Tuts+</a>&nbsp;for access to our library of hundreds of eBooks. With a Yearly subscription, you can download up to five eBooks per month, while the Yearly Pro subscription gives you unlimited access.</p>\r\n", "content_introduction"=>"<h3>1. Social Media Mining With R</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This essential guide will give you hands-on experience with generating insights from social media data.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/social-media-mining-with-r?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Social Media Mining With R</a>&nbsp;provides detailed instructions on how to obtain, process, and analyze a&nbsp;variety of socially-generated data, while teaching you some theory to help you accurately interpret your findings. You will learn R code and see examples of data you can use to undertake your own analyses of business, social, or political data.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Extending Symfony2 Web Application Framework</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/extending-symfony2-web-application-framework?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">This eBook</a> offers solutions to all your Symfony extension problems. You will get to grips with all the extension points that Symfony, Twig, and Doctrine offer, and understand how you can use them to achieve cleaner, better structured, and reusable code for your application.&nbsp;Whether you have already written extensions for Symfony2 or not, this book will be a useful guide to all the possible types of extensions, and how you can use them in your own applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Getting Started With SOQL</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In <a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/getting-started-with-soql?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Getting Started With SOQL</a>, you will learn the optimum way to write complex SOQL statements. Beginning with basic SOQL statements, you will progress quickly onto more advanced statements, such as how to filter multiselect picklist values to escape sequences. By the end, you&#39;ll be&nbsp;a SOQL expert, able to write SOQL statements in an optimized and effective way.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Alfresco CMIS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Content Management Interoperability Services (CMIS) standard provides a standard way for content management systems to talk to each other, and the Alfresco CMIS implementation is the basis for many existing CMIS applications. Our new eBook,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/alfresco-cmis?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Alfresco CMIS</a>,&nbsp;provides you with a number of clear step-by-step exercises that will help you take advantage of the power of CMIS, and give you a good foundation in using it via HTTP/XML, Java, or&nbsp;scripting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Pentaho Analytics for MongoDB</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/pentaho-analytics-for-mongodb?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Pentaho Analytics for MongoDB</a> will teach you MongoDB and Pentaho integration points, and cover the developer skills you need to create analytic solutions that deliver insight for your organization.&nbsp;Starting with how to install, configure, and develop content in both Pentaho and MongoDB, this book will give you the complete&nbsp;range of skills needed to gain insight into MongoDB data using Pentaho&nbsp;Business&nbsp;Analytics.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Learning Pentesting for Android Devices</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/learning-pentesting-for-android-devices?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Learning Pentesting for Android Devices</a>&nbsp;will take you from the very basic level of Android Security right through to penetration testing and auditing Android. It is a step-by-step guide, covering a variety of techniques that you can use to perform real life penetration testing on Android devices and applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>7. Apache Solr High Performance</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Apache Solr is one of the most popular open source search servers available on the web.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/apache-solr-high-performance?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Apache Solr High Performance</a>&nbsp;will help you achieve optimized Solr instances, especially in terms of performance.&nbsp;You will learn everything you need to know to achieve a high performing Solr instance or set of instances, as well as how to troubleshoot common problems you might face while working with single or multiple Solr servers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>8. Google Apps Script for Beginners</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Apps Script is a JavaScript-based programming language that works on the cloud and is 100% free to use. It provides all the tools necessary for Google services to work.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://code.tutsplus.com/ebooks/google-apps-script-for-beginners?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost-ebooks&amp;utm_content=2014-11&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost-ebooks_2014-11\" target=\"_self\">Our new eBook</a>&nbsp;helps you get started with Google Apps Script through clear explanation and working examples. You will create custom functions in your spreadsheets, design your own forms, filter your emails, and publish web applications that you can use every day.</p>\r\n", "content_main"=>"", "content_short_introduction"=>"Do you want to learn more about the Google Apps Script? How about extending the Symfony 2 web application framework, or getting started with SOQL? Our latest batch of eBooks will teach you all you need to know about these topics and more.", "demo_link"=>"", "github_link"=>"http://onlinebook.in", "mode"=>"Beginner", "tutorial_order"=>1, "primary_category"=>"Web Development", "publish_date"=> Time.now.utc, "related_link"=>nil, "review_comment"=>nil, "reviewed_by"=>nil, "reviewed_date"=>nil, "series_id"=>0, "state"=>"Publish", "time"=>"Medium", "title"=>"New eBooks Available for Subscribers", "total_view"=>0, "tutorial_picture_content_type"=>nil, "tutorial_picture_file_name"=>nil, "tutorial_picture_file_size"=>nil, "tutorial_picture_updated_at"=>nil, "tutorial_type"=>"Free", "updated_by_writer"=>Time.now.utc, "user_id"=>1, "video_url"=>"", "vote_up"=>0)


